                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Italy/48</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                            <gloss type="to">Blair &amp; Co.</gloss>, Incorporated</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-09-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1925</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In confirmation of Mr. Young’s<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d315fn4">Arthur N. Young, Economic Adviser, Department of
                        State.</note> statement to Mr. Sheldon<note n="5" xml:id="d315fn5"
                        >Representative of Blair &amp; Co.</note> on August 31, in response to Mr.
                    Sheldon’s inquiry concerning the attitude of the Department of State in regard
                    to the flotation of Italian industrial securities in the United States, I beg to
                    say that this Department would not view such financing with favor at the present
                    time.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph C. Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
